WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. It's Tuesday, March thirty-first, twenty twenty-six. It's

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
payday. The carpet installers arrive at nine. Ben is presumably

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
asleep on your couch. And the President of the United

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
States just threatened to destroy Iran's desalination plants. Let's get

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
into it. Weather first. Jefferson City today: eighty-five degrees with

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
a chance of thunderstorms this afternoon, south winds gusting to

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
thirty-two miles per hour. Tonight drops to fifty-nine with an

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
eighty-two percent chance of storms. Wednesday is a washout —

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
seventy-five degrees and eighty-six percent chance of rain. Good Artemis-watching-from-the-couch

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
weather. Over in Tacoma, Katelyn gets fifty-six and partly sunny

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
today. Wednesday is fifty-one and rainy. She's off Thursday, which

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
is sunny. Your calendar. Today is busy. Carpet install runs

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
nine A-M to two P-M — Ben can handle the

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
installers while you're at work. Lunch with Gina at eleven-thirty.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
O-A M-L-A grads follow-up meeting at two. Budget and Planning

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
management meeting at three. Don't forget: Katelyn explicitly requested carpet

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
photos. Tomorrow, Wednesday, is a triple-header. Apple turns fifty. Karen

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
announces her retirement at eleven A-M. And Artemis Two launches

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
at five twenty-four P-M Central — first humans around the

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
moon since nineteen seventy-two. Then Thursday. Thursday is everything. Anthropic

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
pilot meeting at nine A-M. B-R training at two. Dinner

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
with Alex, Chris, and Dustin at six. And the government's

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
appeal deadline for the Anthropic case — the same day

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
you pitch Claude to your colleagues. The writers of this

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
simulation are not being subtle. Text messages. Katelyn was active

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
from about two-thirty P-M through midnight Monday. She's dog-sitting —

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
Wolf, Pippa, and the boys — and made them all

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
sleep in her room, which Wolf was not pleased about.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
Pippa, apparently, is the fastest outdoor dog. You two discussed

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Australia being terrifying, yoga that neither of you actually does,

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
and she wants carpet photos tomorrow. Don't forget. Dustin dropped

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
a bombshell in the group chat. Crossley is moving to

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
the Netherlands. His family is leaving the U-S, citing politics.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
Given the war, the shutdown, and the general state of

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
things, that's less "fleeing" and more "reading the room." Dustin

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
also shared the legislative shit weekends schedule — West April

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
eleventh and twelfth, East April eighteenth and nineteenth. And Chris

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
had a late-night spiritual experience discovering Tacolate. Quote: "I love

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
capitalism." Ben arrived last night. The brothers immediately started gaming

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Minecraft. He's here for the carpet install, which is a

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
two-day commitment. Alex went deep on robot vacuums — he

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
owns an iRobot Roomba i-seven-plus and flagged a new one

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
with Matter and HomeKit support. Also, Shayla is confirmed moving

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
this summer. Alex asked you to act like you don't

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
know. Chris shared Missouri Senate floor color — a senator

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
named Joe Nicola publicly defied a federal executive order, saying

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
he "was not elected to be a puppet of the

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
federal government." Welcome to the resistance, apparently. Now the big

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
stories. Iran, day thirty-two. This morning's lead from Axios: Trump

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
threatened to, quote, "completely obliterate" Iran's power plants, oil wells,

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
and desalination plants. A senior official told Axios the idea

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
is to use strikes so Iran has no water. International

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
humanitarian law explicitly prohibits attacks on civilian water infrastructure. Meanwhile,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
Iran struck a Kuwaiti desalination plant and an oil tanker

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
off Kuwait's coast. Gulf nations depend on desalination for fresh

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
water. This is no longer just a U-S-Iran war —

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
it's a regional water crisis. Gas crossed four dollars nationally

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
for the first time since twenty twenty-two. Brent crude hit

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
about one-fifteen, posting a fifty-five percent monthly gain — the

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
largest in the contract's history. Europe is panicking. Eurozone inflation

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
hit two point five percent. The E-U energy chief told

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
Europeans to "consider traveling less." Chile hiked petrol prices fifty

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
percent. B-Y-D searches are up fivefold in the U-K. D-H-S

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
shutdown, day forty-six. T-S-A workers are finally getting paid. Multiple

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
officers confirmed receiving paychecks Monday — the first since funding

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
lapsed on Valentine's Day. Five hundred and ten workers have

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
quit permanently. Congress is on recess. No resolution before mid-April.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
Quick status board. Anthropic versus the Pentagon: appeal deadline Thursday.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
All four watchlist career roles still posted. SpaceX I-P-O: Bloomberg

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
says they may file confidential paperwork with the S-E-C this

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
week. One point seven-five trillion dollar valuation. Nasdaq changed rules

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
to fast-track their listing. Artemis Two: countdown is live, eighty

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
percent favorable weather, launch tomorrow five twenty-four P-M Central. City

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
of Seattle economics and revenue analyst — day fourteen. If

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
you're going to apply, this week is the week. Tech

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
and A-I roundup. OpenAI killed Sora. The video platform, the

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
developer A-P-Is, and all video features in ChatGPT — gone.

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Sam Altman announced a pivot to productivity tools and a

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
ChatGPT super-app. This is Anthropic's enterprise focus forcing OpenAI's hand.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
Apple plans to open Siri to rival A-I assistants in

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
i-O-S twenty-seven. Claude, Gemini, and others will integrate via the

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
App Store. Apple takes thirty percent of subscription revenue year

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
one, fifteen after. This is the aggregator playbook — own

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
the customer, commoditize the complement. Apple is also paying rare

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
out-of-cycle bonuses of several hundred thousand dollars to iPhone hardware

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
designers to stop them from leaving for OpenAI. And Rec

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
Room — once valued at three point five billion dollars

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
— is shutting down, because it turns out that letting

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
children in V-R headsets play for free is not, in

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
fact, a business model. Closing thought. Americans who spend five

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
or more hours a day on social media are fifteen

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
percentage points less likely to believe democracy is the best

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
form of government, which tracks — because if you spent

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
five hours a day on social media, you probably wouldn't

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
believe anything is the best form of anything. Crossley is

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
headed to the Netherlands. Chris discovered Tacolate at midnight. Ben

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
is on your couch. The carpet goes in today. Tomorrow

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
Apple turns fifty, humans go to the moon, and Karen

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
retires. Thursday you pitch Claude while the government decides Claude's

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:39.200
future. Happy payday, Jacob. Take the carpet photos.
